1
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:07,520
I came here to apologize to you.

2
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:10,760
I'm sorry.

3
00:02:10,760 --> 00:02:12,760
I messed things up.

4
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,520
Don't be upset anymore.

5
00:02:18,720 --> 00:02:19,880
I'll figure something out.

6
00:02:21,760 --> 00:02:23,360
There's always a way, right?

7
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:28,880
You take care of yourselves.

8
00:02:32,720 --> 00:02:33,520
I'm off.

9
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,520
I just got the notice.

10
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,320
This thing has blown up too much.

11
00:02:57,320 --> 00:02:59,440
The higher-ups ordered us to close and fix things.

12
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,880
Now that it's come to this,

13
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,400
my little temple's too small

14
00:03:04,400 --> 00:03:06,080
to hold big shots like you two.

15
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,400
Please go find better prospects, alright?

16
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:10,880
I did it today to save that little kid.

17
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,920
That counts as a Good Samaritan act, right?

18
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:16,360
Director, if the kid had really gotten hurt,

19
00:03:16,360 --> 00:03:17,640
we'd be the ones held responsible.

20
00:03:17,640 --> 00:03:19,640
I know it was a Good Samaritan act,

21
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:20,600
but right now,

22
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:23,240
she really did scare that kid into the hospital.

23
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:24,360
And the worst part is,

24
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:26,040
now everybody knows

25
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,800
our park's bear is just someone in a costume.

26
00:03:27,800 --> 00:03:28,960
How do we deal with that?

27
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,640
Wasn't the costume your idea?

28
00:03:30,640 --> 00:03:32,160
I told you from the start it was deceiving the guests.

29
00:03:32,160 --> 00:03:33,200
Was this your call or not?

30
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:35,040
And now that it went wrong, it's all our fault?

31
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:37,040
You're just using and discarding us, you know?

32
00:03:37,040 --> 00:03:38,480
You two are being way too harsh.

33
00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:40,120
Is it that we're being harsh,

34
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,880
or that you handled this so badly?

35
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:45,080
We worked so hard, from rehearsals to performing,

36
00:03:45,360 --> 00:03:46,440
for all this time.

37
00:03:46,440 --> 00:03:48,080
We were going permanent tomorrow,

38
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:49,720
and today you're firing us.

39
00:03:49,720 --> 00:03:50,840
What is this about?

40
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,120
It's all on me.

41
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,760
If someone takes the fall, it's me.

42
00:03:55,040 --> 00:03:56,360
This isn't about who takes the fall.

43
00:03:56,480 --> 00:03:57,720
The park's about to shut down,

44
00:03:57,720 --> 00:03:59,040
and I'm losing my job too.

45
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:00,480
It's all your fault.

46
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:02,480
Everything was fine before you showed up.

47
00:04:02,480 --> 00:04:04,440
Then you arrived, and this huge mess happened.

48
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:09,920
What? Got a problem with that?

49
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:10,960
Wu Huilian.

50
00:04:18,280 --> 00:04:20,360
You're picking on honest folks, you know that?

51
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:22,080
Honest folks go to prison, do they?

52
00:04:22,080 --> 00:04:23,440
Say that again.

53
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,800
You should be thanking me.

54
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:26,360
I gave you a way to put food on the table.

55
00:04:26,640 --> 00:04:27,560
Say that again.

56
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,080
I said it, so what?

57
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:28,600
Auntie Lan, Auntie Lan.

58
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:29,680
Stop fighting, stop fighting.

59
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:30,360
You've gone too far.

60
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:31,320
You hit me, you hit me!

61
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:32,920
We worked so hard,

62
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:34,360
finally about to go permanent.

63
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,280
Okay, Auntie Lan, go home first, go home.

64
00:04:37,440 --> 00:04:38,240
Just go home.

65
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,920
Yiran, head back first, head back.

66
00:04:41,280 --> 00:04:41,560
Let's go.

67
00:04:41,560 --> 00:04:42,520
Just go home, go home.

68
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,680
Go home, go home.

69
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,840
Director, calm down too.

70
00:04:55,080 --> 00:04:57,640
So is there any room to smooth this over?

71
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:01,360
Let's go ask the kid's mom at the hospital first.

72
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,320
Come with me.

73
00:05:04,720 --> 00:05:05,520
Okay.

74
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,040
Scrap collection!

75
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,640
Collecting scrap! Got any junk to sell?

76
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:24,520
Scrap collector here!

77
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:44,080
Running around all day.

78
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:47,680
That was way too much exercise.

79
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:48,520
So tired.

80
00:05:49,440 --> 00:05:50,920
I'm absolutely starving.

81
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,520
Let's go eat, then.

82
00:05:52,520 --> 00:05:53,280
I'm not eating.

83
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:54,840
I lost my job,

84
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:55,920
and you think I feel like eating?

85
00:06:03,560 --> 00:06:06,120
You're the one who knows you're hungry.

86
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:09,440
An army marches on its stomach.

87
00:06:09,760 --> 00:06:11,640
Skip one meal and you're famished.

88
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,320
Come on, come on, let's eat.

89
00:06:24,160 --> 00:06:24,960
Damn it.

90
00:06:30,840 --> 00:06:33,560
I'm a bear, I'm a bear.

91
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,160
So silly.

92
00:06:43,960 --> 00:06:46,560
I'm a bear, I'm a bear.

93
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:47,920
I'm a big old bear.

94
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,840
Xiao Fan, Xiao Fan.

95
00:06:50,480 --> 00:06:51,280
Xiao Fan.

96
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:57,880
Director, I'm reviewing today's footage.

97
00:06:58,080 --> 00:07:00,120
I was right about you.

98
00:07:00,120 --> 00:07:01,760
This Returning Youth program,

99
00:07:01,760 --> 00:07:04,120
the station put a big budget into it,

100
00:07:04,240 --> 00:07:05,640
so you need to give it your all.

101
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,240
Don't worry, Director.

102
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:11,040
Oh right, there's this.

103
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:13,560
This is the new tea from this year.

104
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:15,720
Take it home for your dad to try.

105
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:18,040
And say hi to him for me.

106
00:07:19,320 --> 00:07:21,640
Director, I can't accept this.

107
00:07:21,640 --> 00:07:22,840
My dad would scold me.

108
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:27,000
Without Chairman Fan,

109
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:28,200
we wouldn't be where we are today.

110
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:31,040
Remember to send him my regards.

111
00:07:33,040 --> 00:07:33,840
Director.

112
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,840
Tomorrow I'll be filming at another location.

113
00:07:36,040 --> 00:07:37,640
Just handle things as you see fit.

114
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:38,880
I trust you.

115
00:07:39,360 --> 00:07:41,480
Anyway, keep an eye on Chen Baixi.

116
00:07:41,960 --> 00:07:43,040
And this too.

117
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:46,040
Yes.

118
00:07:47,120 --> 00:07:49,040
It's Chen Baixi.

119
00:07:52,520 --> 00:07:53,320
What?

120
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,320
Say that again.

121
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:58,840
Borrow?

122
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:00,840
Borrow 200,000?

123
00:08:02,520 --> 00:08:03,640
Two hundred...

124
00:08:08,440 --> 00:08:09,960
You little brat.

125
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:13,040
Have you been dating a girl behind my back?

126
00:08:13,480 --> 00:08:14,320
No.

127
00:08:14,640 --> 00:08:15,840
Then what's going on?

128
00:08:20,040 --> 00:08:22,520
Something happened at the zoo.

129
00:08:24,120 --> 00:08:25,160
So what do you have to say now?

130
00:08:25,160 --> 00:08:26,480
Look at what happened to my kid!

131
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:29,160
Ma'am, I sincerely apologize to you.

132
00:08:29,160 --> 00:08:30,520
I'm truly sorry.

133
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,680
I neglected my duty.

134
00:08:31,680 --> 00:08:33,240
I really never expected this.

135
00:08:33,240 --> 00:08:34,840
There's plenty you never expected.

136
00:08:34,840 --> 00:08:36,080
You are fully responsible now.

137
00:08:36,880 --> 00:08:38,760
Our management is very strict.

138
00:08:38,760 --> 00:08:39,680
Didn't I just say?

139
00:08:39,680 --> 00:08:41,080
We really never expected

140
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:42,040
that this kid

141
00:08:42,040 --> 00:08:43,960
would climb up there himself.

142
00:08:44,240 --> 00:08:45,040
Right?

143
00:08:47,840 --> 00:08:48,640
Right.

144
00:08:49,360 --> 00:08:50,560
The kid climbed up there on his own.

145
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,680
Check the security footage if you don't believe me.

146
00:08:51,680 --> 00:08:52,960
Why should I check anything?

147
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:54,400
It's entirely your fault.

148
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,800
Look what happened to my kid.

149
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:56,720
It's all because of you.

150
00:08:56,720 --> 00:08:57,920
He's already traumatized.

151
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:59,680
Tell me, how are you going to compensate?

152
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,040
Even the doctor said

153
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,600
your kid just has a surface scratch.

154
00:09:02,600 --> 00:09:03,440
It's not serious.

155
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:04,040
Right.

156
00:09:04,080 --> 00:09:05,440
The kid's nutrition costs

157
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,280
and his treatment costs, I'll cover it all.

158
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:08,240
I'll cover everything myself.

159
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:08,960
How about that?

160
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:10,560
I'm very busy with work.

161
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:11,720
Now I have to take time off.

162
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,040
Plus my lost wages,

163
00:09:13,040 --> 00:09:14,920
and the kid's emotional damages.

164
00:09:14,920 --> 00:09:16,640
Final price: 100,000.

165
00:09:16,920 --> 00:09:17,880
100,000?

166
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,320
This is extortion.

167
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:22,720
You idiot.

168
00:09:24,040 --> 00:09:25,240
We just don't want this blowing up,

169
00:09:25,240 --> 00:09:26,320
so we want to settle privately.

170
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:28,560
And what about the other 100,000?

171
00:09:30,120 --> 00:09:31,680
The zoo shut down for restructuring,

172
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,520
The owner fled overnight.

173
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,040
But the animals can't be left starving,

174
00:09:35,040 --> 00:09:36,280
so I have to buy food for them.

175
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:36,960
And...

176
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,440
What did I tell you back then?

177
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:43,040
Don't take that lousy job.

178
00:09:43,920 --> 00:09:44,840
You, you, you.

179
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:46,600
You're absolutely driving me crazy!

180
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:50,080
Fine, don't lend it to me then.

181
00:09:50,560 --> 00:09:51,360
Come back.

182
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:55,920
Get over here.

183
00:10:01,120 --> 00:10:03,640
I can lend you the money.

184
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:07,440
But I have one condition.

185
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:09,280
What condition?

186
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:12,440
You come back and work at the shop.

187
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:15,800
And from now on, big or small,

188
00:10:15,800 --> 00:10:17,240
you do as I say.

189
00:10:20,520 --> 00:10:21,320
Fine.

190
00:10:21,640 --> 00:10:23,360
I'll start at Paradise Funeral Home tomorrow.

191
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,280
But once I pay back the 200,000,

192
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:25,200
I'm out of here.

193
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:26,840
Why you...

194
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:30,720
When your old man was twelve,

195
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:33,640
I was already traveling all over with your grandpa.

196
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,080
By the time I was your age,

197
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:38,480
I'd already taken over this shop.

198
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:42,360
This is the Chen family trade.

199
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:45,320
We have to secure this livelihood

200
00:10:45,960 --> 00:10:48,760
to honor our ancestors.

201
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:49,640
Dad,

202
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,080
Paradise Funeral Home is yours.

203
00:10:51,080 --> 00:10:52,320
It's not mine.

204
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:53,560
Working in the funeral business,

205
00:10:53,560 --> 00:10:54,720
I get no sense of fulfillment.

206
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:57,240
And what would give you fulfillment, huh?

207
00:10:57,640 --> 00:11:01,080
Acting like little animals all day does?

208
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,480
You ignore honest work

209
00:11:03,480 --> 00:11:06,080
and do nothing but shady jobs.

210
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,640
What do you mean, shady jobs?

211
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,440
Being an actor is my dream.

212
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:10,600
Dream, my ass.

213
00:11:11,040 --> 00:11:11,840
If you ask me,

214
00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:13,840
you're just taking shortcuts.

215
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:16,880
Boss Chen, no job is beneath another.

216
00:11:17,040 --> 00:11:18,240
So the funeral business is honest work,

217
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,680
but being an actor isn't?

218
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,840
In this world,

219
00:11:20,840 --> 00:11:23,120
whether bringing a role to life or laying someone to rest,

220
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,640
it all takes real skill.

221
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:30,760
I sent you to college

222
00:11:30,760 --> 00:11:32,560
so you'd study hard,

223
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,440
not so you'd learn to talk back.

224
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,880
I'm trying to reason with you here.

225
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:36,640
Cut the nonsense.

226
00:11:38,040 --> 00:11:39,320
Tomorrow morning,

227
00:11:39,320 --> 00:11:40,640
six o'clock,

228
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,960
be at work on time.

229
00:11:44,040 --> 00:11:45,040
Leave the snacks.

230
00:11:45,920 --> 00:11:47,080
As for you,

231
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:47,720
get the hell out.

232
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:19,720
I was but a wanderer of Wolong Ridge

233
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,440
What are you hiding in my room for?

234
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:32,160
Still haven't kicked that eavesdropping habit?

235
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:32,960
Have you?

236
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,520
None of your business.

237
00:12:36,440 --> 00:12:37,240
Bro.

238
00:12:37,640 --> 00:12:40,840
Congrats on jumping from one hellhole to another.

239
00:12:46,440 --> 00:12:49,120
I know you never liked our line of work.

240
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,040
But Dad's getting old now.

241
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,920
He really needs someone to come back and help.

242
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:54,240
Well, have you ever heard the saying,

243
00:12:54,240 --> 00:12:56,160
Wealth never lasts three generations?

244
00:12:56,440 --> 00:12:58,440
That rule doesn't apply to our trade.

245
00:12:58,880 --> 00:13:01,080
Five thousand years of Chinese civilization,

246
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:02,560
and our trade's always been a money-maker.

247
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:04,440
Then again,

248
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:06,560
you and Dad are the same kind of person.

249
00:13:06,560 --> 00:13:07,880
Both pig-headed.

250
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:09,760
You both learn things the hard way.

251
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:12,240
How am I anything like him?

252
00:13:12,240 --> 00:13:13,040
I'm taller than him.

253
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:14,040
And better-looking too.

254
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:14,680
Let me tell you,

255
00:13:14,680 --> 00:13:16,040
back when I was in Beijing,

256
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:19,080
they all called me the Andy Lau of Lecang.

257
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:20,760
Mr. Andy Lau,

258
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,880
you're daydreaming before you're even asleep.

259
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,040
This one's not for you.

260
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:25,960
Read this one.

261
00:13:28,040 --> 00:13:28,920
Good night.

262
00:13:28,920 --> 00:13:30,680
I'm off to grab a snack with Pops.

263
00:14:27,840 --> 00:14:28,640
Pops

264
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,040
I wish you were still here

265
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:00,760
It's an auspicious day

266
00:15:10,000 --> 00:15:11,120
Did you all forget?

267
00:15:13,280 --> 00:15:14,280
Forget it

268
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:17,520
I'll just reward myself

269
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:28,920
A little to the left

270
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,000
Amin, be careful

271
00:15:32,920 --> 00:15:33,680
Pops, you go over there

272
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:34,440
I'll hold it

273
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:36,440
Girl, I don't need your help

274
00:15:36,440 --> 00:15:37,240
Stand aside

275
00:15:39,640 --> 00:15:40,720
Hey, is this for me?

276
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:41,440
I'm hungry

277
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,200
Amin, veggie buns

278
00:15:47,840 --> 00:15:49,080
So stingy

279
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:55,280
Didn't I tell you to be here by six?

280
00:15:55,280 --> 00:15:56,840
Why are you only showing up now?

281
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,600
I just helped an old lady cross the road

282
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,480
It's nine o'clock already

283
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:02,160
How on earth did you help her?

284
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:03,760
