00:33:00,280 --> 00:33:02,320
When I was your age,

575
00:33:04,120 --> 00:33:05,760
my pops passed away too.

576
00:33:09,720 --> 00:33:12,200
He passed in the summer as well,

577
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:14,240
so he was buried very quickly.

578
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:20,120
I didn't even get to see him one last time.

579
00:33:28,560 --> 00:33:30,880
We'll never know

580
00:33:32,720 --> 00:33:35,160
whether tomorrow or disaster comes first.

581
00:33:37,760 --> 00:33:39,360
I lost my pops too.

582
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,720
I understand how you feel.

583
00:33:42,560 --> 00:33:43,440
Yesterday...

584
00:33:43,920 --> 00:33:46,120
Just yesterday I was on the phone with my dad.

585
00:33:46,120 --> 00:33:48,000
I told him

586
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,640
I got into college.

587
00:33:50,800 --> 00:33:52,440
I never expected

588
00:33:52,440 --> 00:33:53,600
that today...

589
00:33:53,600 --> 00:33:56,000
that today he'd be gone.

590
00:34:03,240 --> 00:34:04,320
Go ahead and cry.

591
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,520
After today,

592
00:34:09,240 --> 00:34:11,160
you'll be the pillar of the family.

593
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,160
In your dad's place,

594
00:34:14,720 --> 00:34:16,280
you have to take good care of the family.

595
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,480
I'm so happy!

596
00:34:26,480 --> 00:34:28,480
My kid got into college!

597
00:34:37,800 --> 00:34:38,600
And also,

598
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:42,240
last night he was so incredibly happy.

599
00:34:44,120 --> 00:34:45,520
He said he had no regrets.

600
00:34:45,520 --> 00:34:47,600
Every sacrifice he made was worth it.

601
00:34:49,040 --> 00:34:50,520
He wants you to know

602
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:54,440
that you are his pride.

603
00:35:07,920 --> 00:35:10,040
Dad

604
00:35:11,640 --> 00:35:13,240
Dad

605
00:35:13,240 --> 00:35:15,480
I miss you

606
00:35:15,920 --> 00:35:18,360
I want you to come back

607
00:35:19,880 --> 00:35:23,480
Dad, Dad

608
00:35:27,440 --> 00:35:29,320
Dad

609
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:32,760
Dad

610
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:38,240
Come back

611
00:35:38,240 --> 00:35:40,600
I'm begging you, Dad

612
00:35:41,800 --> 00:35:45,000
Dad

613
00:35:57,000 --> 00:35:58,280
Who's this kid?

614
00:36:01,280 --> 00:36:03,040
Chen Baixi, my high school classmate.

615
00:36:04,480 --> 00:36:05,440
His dad

616
00:36:05,440 --> 00:36:06,760
sent funeral home ads

617
00:36:06,760 --> 00:36:08,440
all the way to our company.

618
00:36:08,440 --> 00:36:10,640
From now on, you stay away from this kid.

619
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:15,040
Dad, Chen Baixi goes to college in Beijing.

620
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,440
He's really ambitious.

621
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,120
The son of someone making a living off the dead,

622
00:36:18,120 --> 00:36:19,160
what future could he have?

623
00:36:20,160 --> 00:36:21,280
In our Fan family,

624
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:23,040
your grandpa is a university professor.

625
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:25,400
Your mom and I are both respectable people.

626
00:36:25,400 --> 00:36:27,640
If you really care about your own future,

627
00:36:28,800 --> 00:36:31,320
go on a blind date with Director Wang's son tomorrow.

628
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,640
A blind date?

629
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:38,600
For marriage, listen to your parents.

630
00:36:38,600 --> 00:36:39,760
You won't go wrong.

631
00:36:43,600 --> 00:36:45,360
So just to be of equal standing,

632
00:36:45,360 --> 00:36:47,440
I have to marry a man I don't even like?

633
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:50,160
Like?

634
00:36:50,160 --> 00:36:51,720
Can "like" be spent like money,

635
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,160
or can it feed you?

636
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:58,560
If you really want to date someone,

637
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:01,760
you'd better find someone respectable.

638
00:37:28,040 --> 00:37:42,480
Happy birthday to you

639
00:37:43,520 --> 00:37:44,800
Happy birthday, happy birthday

640
00:37:44,800 --> 00:37:45,760
Happy birthday

641
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:47,600
So you did remember my birthday

642
00:37:47,600 --> 00:37:49,720
We wanted to surprise you, of course

643
00:37:49,720 --> 00:37:53,120
Someone was feeling sorry for herself this morning

644
00:37:53,280 --> 00:37:54,120
This is for me?

645
00:37:56,320 --> 00:37:57,520
A phone

646
00:37:58,480 --> 00:38:00,000
Thank you so much

647
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:01,960
Looks like you do care about me after all

648
00:38:04,160 --> 00:38:05,440
Thank you, Yiran

649
00:38:05,440 --> 00:38:06,040
What did you get me?

650
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:07,680
Open it when you get home

651
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:15,680
Xiaofang

652
00:38:16,360 --> 00:38:17,120
Make a wish

653
00:38:17,400 --> 00:38:18,200
Yes, yes, yes

654
00:38:23,480 --> 00:38:26,880
I hope everyone I love and who loves me

655
00:38:26,880 --> 00:38:28,480
stays safe and sound

656
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:29,840
and becomes wealthy and prosperous.

657
00:38:29,840 --> 00:38:31,480
As long as your dad won't agree

658
00:38:31,480 --> 00:38:33,520
you two can forget about getting married

659
00:38:34,240 --> 00:38:35,520
My sister can't stand being treated like this

660
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:38,360
Sweetie

661
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,400
Pops

662
00:38:40,880 --> 00:38:42,480
Birthday girl

663
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:46,640
Here are your longevity noodles

664
00:38:46,640 --> 00:38:47,840
Thank you, Pops

665
00:38:47,840 --> 00:38:49,560
Now that we have longevity noodles

666
00:38:51,320 --> 00:38:54,000
here's a red packet too

667
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:57,080
It's a big one

668
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:57,960
Thank you, Pops

669
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:59,640
I love you

670
00:38:59,640 --> 00:39:00,400
Okay, okay

671
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:02,480
You're all grown up, that's still so mushy

672
00:39:03,840 --> 00:39:05,680
Alright, dig in then

673
00:39:05,680 --> 00:39:07,120
Pops, I haven't blown out my candles yet

674
00:39:12,400 --> 00:39:13,800
Happy birthday, happy birthday

675
00:39:13,920 --> 00:39:14,800
Take the seat of honor

676
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,520
Come on, come on

677
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:19,680
Sit

678
00:39:19,680 --> 00:39:20,360
Okay

679
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:22,920
So next up, is it

680
00:39:22,920 --> 00:39:25,320
the much-awaited cake-cutting?

681
00:39:26,040 --> 00:39:27,600
Cut the cake, cut the cake

682
00:39:29,040 --> 00:39:30,360
The first slice

683
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:32,880
has to go to my

684
00:39:32,880 --> 00:39:34,320
most, most, most

685
00:39:34,320 --> 00:39:35,880
beloved dad

686
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,360
Okay, okay, okay

687
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:40,800
The second slice goes to my

688
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:42,920
beautiful, kind best friend

689
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:45,440
Miss Li Yiran

690
00:39:45,440 --> 00:39:46,360
Thank you

691
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,840
The third slice, here

692
00:39:48,840 --> 00:39:50,920
You bought me the phone, that was too much

693
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:51,760
It's nothing

694
00:39:52,040 --> 00:39:53,800
The fourth slice, Xiao Zhou

695
00:39:54,200 --> 00:39:55,120
Thank you

696
00:39:55,120 --> 00:39:56,400
I sent your gift by transfer, okay?

697
00:39:57,560 --> 00:39:59,360
The fifth slice is for myself

698
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:02,120
Happy birthday

699
00:40:05,840 --> 00:40:06,680
Who ordered the cake for me?

700
00:40:06,680 --> 00:40:07,400
I did, I did

701
00:40:07,400 --> 00:40:08,080
Really?

702
00:40:08,080 --> 00:40:09,360
I arranged everything

703
00:40:09,360 --> 00:40:09,760
Right?

704
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:11,160
Yes, you arranged it

705
00:40:11,160 --> 00:40:12,360
That's very thoughtful of you.

706
00:40:14,960 --> 00:40:15,720
It's delicious

707
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:19,560
Delicious

708
00:40:19,560 --> 00:40:20,880
Cheer up a little

709
00:40:21,720 --> 00:40:22,800
Cheer up

710
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:27,840
Exactly

711
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:31,280
The most important thing in life is to be happy

712
00:40:33,280 --> 00:40:34,320
It's your birthday and you're smearing it on me?

713
00:40:34,320 --> 00:40:35,440
That's right, it's your birthday

714
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:37,480
so how can we skip the cake smearing?

715
00:40:37,480 --> 00:40:38,800
Happy birthday

716
00:40:45,760 --> 00:40:47,000
I don't know

717
00:40:47,000 --> 00:40:49,280
whether everything we're living through

718
00:40:49,280 --> 00:40:50,880
is as beautiful as the wishes

719
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,360
we once made

720
00:40:53,160 --> 00:40:54,480
But I finally understand

721
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:56,440
whether tragedy

722
00:40:56,880 --> 00:40:57,960
or comedy

723
00:40:58,560 --> 00:40:59,840
joys and sorrows, partings and reunions

724
00:40:59,840 --> 00:41:01,240
birth, aging, sickness and death

725
00:41:01,760 --> 00:41:04,160
this fleeting, dreamlike world

726
00:41:04,160 --> 00:41:06,040
we must experience it all, one by one

727
00:41:06,560 --> 00:41:08,760
And the only thing we can do

728
00:41:08,760 --> 00:41:10,840
is in every moment of time

729
00:41:10,840 --> 00:41:12,760
to hold each other close

730
00:41:22,080 --> 00:41:26,240
Oh, my hardworking mother

731
00:41:27,360 --> 00:41:28,840
It's a man

732
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:33,680
Oh, my hardworking husband

733
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:35,240
It's an old man

734
00:41:35,440 --> 00:41:41,240
Oh, my hardworking father

